<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Ending With -EST — Scrabble Suffix Scoring Guide</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -EST suffix creates superlative adjectives — the quickest, the thickest, the greatest. At 3 base points with common tiles E(1)+S(1)+T(1), -EST transforms one-syllable adjectives into 7-8 letter words that naturally hit bingo territory. It's also one of the most reliable hook endings in Scrabble.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -EST Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E(1)+S(1)+T(1)</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">800+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid -EST words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4–9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter length range</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>The -EST suffix uses three of the most common tiles in Scrabble — E (12 in bag), S (4 in bag), and T (6 in bag). This means you'll frequently have the letters available. The scoring power comes from the root adjective: QUICK+EST uses Q(10)+K(5), THICK+EST uses H(4)+K(5), and BLACK+EST uses B(3)+K(5).</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Scoring -EST Words</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
