<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Short -EST Words for Tight Boards</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BEST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">REST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NEST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WEST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TEST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FEST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span></span>
</div>

<p>Four-letter -EST words are essential for parallel plays and board control. WEST and FEST both score 7 points thanks to W(4) and F(4), while BEST hits 6 with B(3). These short words also accept extensive front-hooks: REST becomes CREST, NEST becomes HONEST, TEST becomes CONTEST.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Extend -ER to -EST:</span> If an opponent plays QUICK+ER, you can often hook EST over it or extend the same root. Knowing both comparative and superlative forms doubles your options from the same root tiles.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target K-words for bingos:</span> The highest -EST words all contain K(5): QUICKEST (23), THICKEST (17), BLACKEST (16). If you draw K, hold E+S+T and look for a 4-letter adjective root.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use short -EST for defense:</span> BEST, WEST, FEST placed adjacent to premium squares can block opponents while scoring decently. Their common tiles mean they rarely strand your rack.</p>
  </div>
</div>

